This paper deals with the analysis of logic programs, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on abstract domains for detecting sharing and linearity information, which could also be classified under the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of abstract unification algorithms, which could be classified under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper discusses the interaction between sharing and linearity, which could be classified under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of abstract unification operators, which could be classified under the formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
